<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-06-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-06-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="401" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d401">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.51/520</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Minister of Haiti</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Haiti</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-28">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 28, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: I have the honor to
                            inform your excellency that the President of Haiti has agreed to the
                            proposition made by the President of the United States to appoint Mr. A.
                            J. Maumus as Receiver General and Mr. W. S. Matthews as Deputy Receiver
                            General of the Customs of the Republic of Haiti.</p>
                        <p>The President of Haiti hopes soon to have the opportunity and pleasure of
                            also appointing the Financial Adviser as provided by Article II of the
                            Convention of September 16, 1915, between the Republic of Haiti and the
                            United States of America.</p>
                        <p>Be pleased, [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Solon Ménos</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>